PART 4: THE THREE REGULAR TOURNAMENT CLASSES
======================================================================
Circulant connection sets grouped by α₂:
  α₂=7: [([1, 2, 4], 189), ([3, 5, 6], 189)]
  α₂=14: [([1, 2, 3], 175), ([1, 3, 5], 175), ([1, 4, 5], 175), ([2, 3, 6], 175), ([2, 4, 6], 175), ([4, 5, 6], 175)]

Total regular tournaments: 2640
Circulant contributions:
  S=[1, 2, 3]: |Aut|=7, orbit=720, α₂=14, H=175
  S=[1, 2, 4]: |Aut|=21, orbit=240, α₂=7, H=189
  S=[1, 3, 5]: |Aut|=7, orbit=720, α₂=14, H=175
  S=[1, 4, 5]: |Aut|=7, orbit=720, α₂=14, H=175
  S=[2, 3, 6]: |Aut|=7, orbit=720, α₂=14, H=175
  S=[2, 4, 6]: |Aut|=7, orbit=720, α₂=14, H=175
  S=[3, 5, 6]: |Aut|=21, orbit=240, α₂=7, H=189
  S=[4, 5, 6]: |Aut|=7, orbit=720, α₂=14, H=175

Non-circulant regular tournaments?
  Distinct class: S=[1, 2, 3], orbit=720, α₂=14
  Distinct class: S=[1, 2, 4], orbit=240, α₂=7
  Total from distinct circulant classes: 960
  Total regular tournaments: 2640
  Non-circulant: 1680

  There ARE non-circulant regular tournaments on n=7!
  The 'middle' class (α₂=10, count=1680) has orbit 1680 = 7!/3
  This means |Aut|=3 — NOT divisible by 7, so NOT circulant!

======================================================================
PART 5: CONNECTION SET ↔ α₂ PATTERN
======================================================================
  S=[1, 2, 3]: α₂=14, sums=[3, 4, 5], prods=[2, 3, 6], AP(d=1)
  S=[1, 2, 4]: α₂= 7, sums=[3, 5, 6], prods=[2, 4, 1], QR
  S=[1, 3, 5]: α₂=14, sums=[4, 6, 1], prods=[3, 5, 1], AP(d=2)
  S=[1, 4, 5]: α₂=14, sums=[5, 6, 2], prods=[4, 5, 6], 
  S=[2, 3, 6]: α₂=14, sums=[5, 1, 2], prods=[6, 5, 4], 
  S=[2, 4, 6]: α₂=14, sums=[6, 1, 3], prods=[1, 5, 3], AP(d=2)
  S=[3, 5, 6]: α₂= 7, sums=[1, 2, 4], prods=[1, 4, 2], NQR
  S=[4, 5, 6]: α₂=14, sums=[2, 3, 4], prods=[6, 3, 2], AP(d=1)

SYNTHESIS:
  The connection set determines the α₂ value for circulant tournaments.
  QR_7 = {1,2,4}: minimizes α₂ (=7) — most "ordered" cycle structure
  NQR_7 = {3,5,6}: also α₂=7 — isomorphic to QR_7 complement
  Max α₂=14 sets: specific 3-element subsets of Z_7 — most "disordered"

  The α₂ spectrum {7, 10, 14} for regular tournaments on n=7
  mirrors the structure of 3-element subsets of Z_7 under
  the natural action of the affine group AGL(1,7).

